shared_text:
Belleville Public Schools
March 22 at 6:58 PM ·

VERY IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT (PLEASE SHARE)

Due to the current precautionary measures recently established by Governor Murphy and in conjunction with flexible concessions to the Open Public Meetings Act, the Belleville Board of Education work session meeting to discuss the preliminary budget scheduled for Wednesday, March 25, 2020 at 4:00 pm will be closed to the public. As always, the meeting will be streamed live from the district Facebook page. If any citizen would like to submit a comment which will be read into the record during the meeting, he/she is requested to submit said question by 2:00 pm on Wednesday, March 25, 2020 to the Board Secretary, Matthew Paladino via electronic correspondence at
Matthew.Paladino@bellevilleschools.org

Thank you.

post_text:
Ethan Laquindanum and Mofeo Kuku recorded double-doubles, Laquindanum scoring 17 points and adding 11 assists and Kuku tallied 14 points and 12 rebounds, and Hector Castro poured in 23 points to lead Belleville to a 73-64 win over the Academy for Urban Leadership Charter in Belleville.

Franklin Rosario scored 24 points and tallied seven rebounds for Urban Leadership (5-2), which led by a 33-28 margin at halftime. Johan Castillo and Frandy Kimenez notched 16 more points each for Urban Leadership.

Belleville (4-5) posted a 31-point third quarter to take the lead. Nasir Bey tallied an additional 17 points for the Buccaneers.

PaySchools Central is just what its name implies—a central hub for all parent payment activities.
To manage school lunches, fees, and activities, parents log in to PaySchools Central online and pay with a link to their bank account or a credit or debit card.

It’s simple—but when you dig deeper, you’ll see that it’s also an incredibly powerful and full-featured tool.
